#define APOXI_BT_OBEX_SYSTEM_CLIENT_SECURITY
 

Default security settings for OBEX client connections over Bluetooth

Detailed description When an OBEX client connection is opened and no security settings are explicitly specified, this constant defines the default security level.

#define APOXI_LIB_ADDON_AFSFAT
 

Enables support for FAT devices

Detailed description To support different FAT devices, these define has to be set. On target, the RootFileSystem afterwards registers the available FAT devices automatically.


Corresponding features:

  • AFSFAT


Define dependencies:

  • APOXI_SDMMCSPI_SUPPORT
  • APOXI_MMCI_SUPPORT (one of these both - depends on HW)

#define APOXI_OBEX_MAX_NO_SELECTIONS
 

Maximum number of concurrently running transport address selection procedures

Detailed description When an OBEX client connection is requested without a transport protocol being specified as part of the client address (wildcard address starting with *://), MMI is notified asynchronously to select a transport. When this procedure is invoked in a reentrant way, APOXI OBEX queues the requests and notifies them one after another. This constant specified the queue size and therefore the maximum reentrancy level.


Corresponding features:

  • N/A


Define dependencies:

  • N/A


Enabled backward compatibility:

  • obsoleted define: N/A
  • obsoleted define cleared out: N/A

#define APOXI_OBEX_MAX_NO_TRANSPORTS
 

Maximum number of transport protocols supported by APOXI OBEX

Detailed description This constant specifies the size of the transport table and therefore the maximum number of transport implementations which can register themselves with APOXI OBEX.


Corresponding features:

  • N/A
